Heart Attack","startTime":null,"eventDescription":"Hailed as the Superband of the century in 1982, Heart Attack was destined for stardom with super hits such as Jerry's Girl, Summer of 67 and Just Like Kevin. Due to lack of copyright knowledge the songs were ripped!!

"We used to matter!" Don Bronze exclaims as we sit talking in his one bedroom apartment overlooking the place that overlooks the Hustler Store. Scratching his blond hair, he pulls out vinyl from behind a makeshift shelf. He shows me records from all the great bands of the 80's and mumbles "I wrote that song, and that song and he stole that from me in a jam session at Guitar Center."

"We were living good for a while then the bottom fell out. Royalty checks stopped and here I am" as he kicks an old pizza box. Now with the downturn in the house painting market and fry slinging the guys have decided to dust off the red leather suits and get back to the rock that once made them famous. "The suit still fits." Don says sitting back in a multicolored beanbag chair. "I lost the cod piece though."

Now after getting on the treadmill and off candy bars they are fitting back into the red leather and adding "Flashback" to their name. These guys are seamless as they play all the great 80's songs that we all know and remember. They are not your typical "cover" band rather than a high energy 80s tribute with supplying the most entertainment value you can fit in red leather. With a sound and visual unmatched in the genre Flashback is taking the concept to a completely different level.

They are now playing exclusive club dates and private parties from Las Vegas to Canada to Florida. If you want set list information or want them for your events leave a message.
